com.barrysheehan.www

Class AbstractThesaurus

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.barrysheehan.www.AbstractThesaurus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WordMap
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Thesaurus

    public abstract class AbstractThesaurus
extends java.lang.Object
implements WordMap
    Implements WordMap to create a thesaurus in which words in the dictionary Set provide possible values for any words added as keys to the wordMap map.

    A dictionary of words as Strings is created as a Set. This Set is then used as a reference when adding words to the Map wordMap. Any text of words added to wordMap is first checked to see whether it contains a word that exists in the dictionary. If so, the words are added to the wordMap. If not, the words are not added to the wordMap.

    Since:
    1.8

    WordMap, Thesaurus

    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractThesaurus

        public AbstractThesaurus(java.lang.String dictionarySource,
                         java.lang.String wordListSource)
        Creates an AbstractThesaurus using the two Strings passed to it.

        The first String passed is the text used to create a dictionary Set. It is first "initialised", during which it should be added to the instance variable dictionaryString. The String stored at dictionaryString is then used to populate both the dictionary Set and the wordMap Map.

        The second String passed is the text used to create a wordMap Map. It is first "initialised", during which it should be added to the instance variable wordMapString. The String stored at wordMapString is then used to add additional words to the wordMap.

        Parameters:
        dictionarySource - text to be used to populate the dictionary Set and initilise the wordMap Map
        wordListSource - text to be used to populate the wordMap Map

      • addWordMapEntries

        public void addWordMapEntries()
        Populates the Map wordMap with the contents of the String stored at wordListString.

        Reads String at wordListString and splits it into lines lines and subsequently words words. The dictionary is checked to determine whether it contains each word. If so, variable dictionaryWord is updated to contain that word. All words on the same line of the text are added as keys to the wordMap, and the dictionaryWord is added as the value of each key.

        Specified by:
        addWordMapEntries in interface WordMap
